# Build context for the sandbox image (Containerfile).
#
# The build context is handed wholesale to the container runtime, so anything listed here would
# otherwise leave the host during `podman build` even though the Containerfile never COPYs it.
# Today it has zero COPY lines, so the correct context is "almost nothing" — but a stale, fat
# context is exactly how a secret ends up somewhere nobody expected, so the exclusions are explicit
# rather than implied by the absence of a COPY.
#
# NOTE for the stage-2 egress proxy: it will `COPY engine/sandbox/egress_policy.py` and
# `engine/sandbox/proxy.py` into the image. Those live under `engine/`, which is NOT excluded here,
# so they will be available. If you ever switch this file to a deny-all (`*`) form, remember that a
# negation cannot re-include a file whose parent DIRECTORY is excluded — the same rule that bites in
# .gitignore.

# --- secrets and credentials ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key

# --- the agent's own data: conversations, memories, tables, traces, files it wrote ---
data/
workspace/
workspaces/
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
created_tools/
created_skills/
artifacts/

# --- personal / operational: deploy.sh carries the server address, notes carry findings ---
scripts/
docs/
.superpowers/
CLAUDE.md
*.log

# --- development cruft, none of it useful to the image ---
.git/
.github/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
tests/
benchmark/
dashboard/
uv.lock
